# Vuetify Guidelines

## Component Usage
- Use Vuetify components instead of custom HTML elements when possible
- Prefer Vuetify's built-in responsive system
- Use Vuetify's color system and theme variables

## Layout Components
- **v-layout**: Main layout wrapper
- **v-navigation-drawer**: Sidebar navigation
- **v-main**: Main content area
- **v-list**: Navigation lists
- **v-list-item**: Individual navigation items

## Form Components
- **v-text-field**: Text inputs with validation
- **v-textarea**: Multi-line text inputs
- **v-form**: Form wrapper with validation
- **v-btn**: Buttons with various styles and states

## Dialog Components
- **v-dialog**: Modal dialogs
- **v-card**: Card containers for dialog content
- **v-card-title**: Dialog titles
- **v-card-text**: Dialog content
- **v-card-actions**: Dialog action buttons

## Grid and Layout
- **v-row** and **v-col**: Use for simple grid layouts
- **CSS Grid**: Use for complex responsive layouts (preferred for dashboard grids)

## Icons
- Use Material Design Icons (MDI) with `mdi-` prefix
- Import from `@mdi/font` package
- Use `v-icon` component for consistent sizing

## Styling
- Use Vuetify's utility classes when possible
- Override Vuetify styles with `:deep()` selector when needed
- Use Vuetify's spacing system (ma-, pa-, etc.)

## Example Usage
```vue
<template>
  <v-dialog v-model="showDialog" max-width="500">
    <v-card>
      <v-card-title class="text-h5">Dialog Title</v-card-title>
      <v-card-text>
        <v-form ref="form">
          <v-text-field
            v-model="formData.name"
            label="Name"
            :rules="[v => !!v || 'Name is required']"
            variant="outlined"
          />
        </v-form>
      </v-card-text>
      <v-card-actions>
        <v-spacer />
        <v-btn @click="showDialog = false">Cancel</v-btn>
        <v-btn color="primary" @click="save">Save</v-btn>
      </v-card-actions>
    </v-card>
  </v-dialog>
</template>
```